# Tailwind CSS v4 - FlowFork Design System

## CSS-First Configuration

Tailwind v4 uses CSS-first configuration in `app/app.css`:

```css
@import "tailwindcss";

@theme {
  --font-sans: "Inter", ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;
  --spacing-xxs: 0.25rem;  /* 4px */
  --spacing-xs: 0.5rem;    /* 8px */
  --spacing-sm: 1rem;      /* 16px */
  --spacing-md: 1.5rem;    /* 24px */
  --spacing-lg: 2rem;      /* 32px */
  --spacing-xl: 3rem;      /* 48px */
}

@theme inline {
  --color-black: #0A0A0A;
  --color-white: #FFFFFF;
  --color-divider: #F5F5F5;
  --color-inactive: #BDBDBD;
}
```

## Design Principles

- **Monochrome foundation**: Interface stays black/white/gray
- **Color = ingredients only**: Use ingredient colors only for food pictograms
- **No bold text**: Use size and spacing for hierarchy, never font-weight
- **No shadows**: Clean, airy feel
- **No uppercase headings**: Feels aggressive

## CSS Variables

Use CSS variables for all colors:

```tsx
// Good: Using design system variables
<div className="bg-[var(--color-background)] text-[var(--color-text-primary)]" />

// Bad: Using hardcoded colors
<div className="bg-white text-black" />
```

## Class Merging

Always use the `cn()` utility for conditional classes:

```typescript
import { cn } from "~/lib/utils";

<div className={cn(
  "base-classes",
  isActive && "active-classes",
  className
)} />
```

## Component Variants with CVA

Use `class-variance-authority` for component variants:

```typescript
import { cva, type VariantProps } from "class-variance-authority";

const buttonVariants = cva("base-classes rounded-full", {
  variants: {
    variant: {
      primary: "bg-[var(--color-btn-primary-bg)] text-[var(--color-btn-primary-text)]",
      secondary: "bg-transparent border border-[var(--color-btn-secondary-border)]",
    },
    size: {
      default: "px-8 py-4",
      sm: "px-6 py-3",
    },
  },
});
```

## Spacing Scale (8px base)

- `spacing-xxs`: 4px - tight inline elements
- `spacing-xs`: 8px - list item padding
- `spacing-sm`: 16px - default gap between related items
- `spacing-md`: 24px - section internal spacing
- `spacing-lg`: 32px - between major sections
- `spacing-xl`: 48px - screen top/bottom padding

## Typography Rules

- Minimum body size: 16px
- Line height: 1.6 for paragraphs, 1.2 for headings
- Letter spacing: -0.5% for large headings, 0% for body
- Font weights: 300 (light) for body, 400 (regular) for headings
